caption: The Druid was great! Nice looking ethnic Irishman serving us. Outdoor seating if you wanted it. Was looking for a "Real Irish" place to eat since we were in the Irishman's capital. As i would call it. My boyfriend had the Shepherds Pie. He said it was satisfactory. I had the Beef Stew which was also very good. The drink I had I wasn' t sure if I would like it; but they proved me wrong on that one. I loved it! It was called The Perfect Pimms. I had to have another it was so good! Only downside  was the parking . Everything else was very very good though. I highly recommend trying this place if you want real Irish food!

The Druid is a Cambridge institution that needs to be supported at all costs. The gentlemen that run this establishment cultivate a level of service and friendship that is seldom seen at any other so-called 'Irish Pub' in the entirety of the Boston metro area.  Besides all that, the atmosphere is spot on, the food is and has always been consistently incredible, trad on weekends is a nice touch, and there is no better place for a Premiere League game.  I can't wait for things to get back to normal post-pandemic so that The Druid can resume what they've been doing so well for so long. I mourn the day I put Cambridge / Somerville in my rearview, but hope to find this place unchanged should I ever return.

DON'T USE YOUR CREDIT CARD AT THE DRUID!!!  You boosted your tips to charge one of us 90 cents more and the other 60 cents more, which is extremely disappointing considering we'd already left normal tips (we have the receipts to prove it). Quite the racket you have going if you do this to everyone and hope they won't remember and notice it days later when the full charge posts to their accounts.  I'm not going to bother with a chargeback over cents, so you win this time, but consider the cost of your customers' repeat business next time you want to squeeze an extra $1.50 out of pouring two beers.  Don't get scammed - there are more reputable businesses with better selection up the block.
